com.samsung.fastcast.msgs

Class CustomEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.fastcast.msgs.CustomEvent

  • public abstract class CustomEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    CustomEvent class is base class for events that can be created outside library by programmer implementing his scenario. This class is similar to MessageBase but it additionally has informations about event name. If you want create your own custom event you have to inherit from this class. You have to name your event using unique string.

    You shouldn't use names used internally:
    "ready", "status", "play", "reclaim", "keydown", "seek", "volume", "bye", "text", "suspend", "restore"
    see: MessageType.
    If you use one of above names it can make troubles in library working.
    Author:
    m.gajewski

      • fillData

        public abstract void fillData(java.lang.Object data)
                       throws JSONException
        Internal abstract method need to be implemented in inherited class.
        This method is used for filling message object with data received from remote device. Parameter data can be either String for simple messages or JSONObject for complex structures.
        Parameters:
        data - String or JSONObject depends on your message.
        Throws:
